# Local dev env overrides. Copy this file to .env and fill in the
# values you need. The Makefile auto-loads .env (via the include
# block at the top), so any target that spawns the server
# (make server / make dev / make smoke) picks the values up.
#
# Make-include syntax rules apply: one KEY=VALUE per line, no quotes
# around values, no inline comments after a value. Lines starting
# with # are comments.

# Application environment. APP_ENV=development opts cookies out of
# the Secure flag so the dev server is reachable over plain HTTP on
# localhost / LAN, and lets the server generate an ephemeral session
# key. Any other value (or leaving it unset) enforces Secure cookies
# and requires SESSION_KEY to be set explicitly — the fail-secure
# default for production-like contexts. The Makefile defaults this to
# development for make server / dev / smoke, so this only needs to be
# uncommented when running the binary directly (go run, debugger, etc.).
# APP_ENV=development

# Directory uploaded media is written under, in a per-quiz subdirectory
# (#936). Defaults to ./media in the working directory, which is fine for
# local dev. Staging and production must point this at a persistent
# writable volume: the distroless image has no writable app filesystem by
# default, so uploads written to the container's ephemeral FS are lost on
# every restart. The directory is created on startup if it does not exist.
# MEDIA_DIR=./media

# Google sign-in. Leave all three blank to keep the feature off (the
# /login/google routes 404 and the button on /login is hidden). To
# enable, create an OAuth client ("Web application") in the Google
# Cloud Console, add http://localhost:8080/login/google/callback as
# an Authorised redirect URI on that client, and paste the
# credentials below.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URL=http://localhost:8080/login/google/callback

# First-admin bootstrap (#1206). On first boot with no admin present, a
# verified admin is created from these two values; once any admin exists
# they are ignored, so leaving them set across restarts is safe. Leave both
# blank to disable. A malformed email or a password shorter than the
# minimum fails startup.
# INITIAL_ADMIN_EMAIL=
# INITIAL_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Require admin approval before a new account can sign in (#1227). Defaults
# to false. When true, a registrant must confirm their email and then wait
# for an admin to approve the account on /admin/players before they can log
# in. Admins are always approved automatically, so turning this on cannot
# lock an operator out. Leave unset or false to let confirmed accounts sign
# in immediately.
# LOGIN_APPROVAL_REQUIRED=false

# Trusted reverse-proxy allow-list for per-IP rate limiting (#463).
# Comma-separated list of CIDR ranges. When a request arrives from
# one of these CIDRs, the X-Forwarded-For header is consulted to find
# the original client IP; otherwise XFF is ignored entirely and the
# limiter buckets on the request peer's address. Empty (the default)
# means "no proxy in front" - the fail-secure choice for a binary
# exposed directly.
# TRUSTED_PROXY_IPS=127.0.0.1/32,::1/128

# Local Playwright e2e worker count, read by test/e2e/playwright.config.ts
# (the Makefile exports .env, so make test-e2e picks it up). The config
# defaults to 4; raise it on a many-core machine for a faster suite (8 was
# the sweet spot on a 12-core box, ~2.8m vs ~5.2m). CI sets its own value (2).
# E2E_WORKERS=8
